hest level. Look at the models of implants shown on augmentations tree - it's real art right there! In addition, I have to mention closed spaces design - you will never find two identical rooms here. They all are filled with those little details that makes those spaces look like actual living quarters - flowers, cards, books, furniture, computers, small notes, wall painting - there is a lot of work put in here! And it all provides this immersion - once you launch the game, you are inside - inside of not-so-distant future, with implants in human body being reality, with large worldwide corporations being more influential than entire countries, with new global problems and conspiracies - and you have the means and ability to get to the bottom of it all. Great job, artists!\n[*] Technical side is also good here, graphics itself looks beautiful and the game runs on high enough FPS (on GTX 1070). The only annoying thing here is level loading. Game world is not seamless and sometimes require loading which takes some time, but it is probably because my game were installed on HDD, not SSD; loading from SSD should be much faster.\n[*] Storyline is not something extraordinary, but again, it is all about small details. While the plot as a whole is not much amazing, there are so many outcomes and variables in each story and side missions that I am thinking of re-playing the game to see them all and experience those different outcomes. You can complete each mission in many ways, and your actions and choices will affect main story (slightly, but notably).\n[*] Side missions deserve an honorable mention here - try to complete them all, it will really worth the hassle. They add a lot of depth in the game world, and they are really hand-made - a story inside a story, and if you will be observant enough, near the end of the game you'll learn how your approach to each mission affected related characters, which adds a really nice conclusion to those missions. \n[/list]\n\nAlright, so about this 65% rating. When the game was just released, fresh, I heard, vaguely, about microtransactions issue the game had, but I did not care enough at the time to understand what all the fuss was about. Well, now I do, I have seen the in-game shop, and yes, you can buy bullets, weapons, Praxis kits and other consumables there; but really, it looks like all the complainers haven't actually played the game at all. If you will play the game how it is meant to be played (meaning you will explore your surroundings and pick up all the stuff laying around), you will never be short of anything. In fact, when I finished the game, I had 20k credits, 20 multitools, 1k various bullets and 10 (!) spare Praxis kits I didn\u2019t even spent because I already had everything for stealth-hacking playstyle I chose to play. \nSo, all the downvotes were just because of possibility to buy some in-game things for real money, and might I remind you, it's not even a multiplayer game! So I don\u2019t really get what the heck this all was about; including microtransactions in the game probably was a bad desicion, but in-game shop availability doesn't eradicate all the amazing work that was put into making the game itself. Therefore, if you missed that game just because you heard of microtransactions - congratulations, you just spoiled yourself this great game for no real reason. \n\nSo, definitely [b]recommend[/b]. If you want to play the game with rich story and fascinating world - it is a game for you. Do not be too sensitive to unfounded accusations that are irrelevant to the game in the first place.\n", "received_for_free": false, "timestamp_created": 1505132949, "written_during_early_access": false, "timestamp_updated": 1505132949, "recommendationid": "34881854", "language": "english", "votes_down": 5, "steam_purchase": true, "weighted_vote_score": "0.508089", "voted_up": true}, {"author": {"last_played": 1505149785, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "num_reviews": 6, "playtime_forever": 2